G\times G\to G\,\,,\,x\cdot g:=g^x:=xgx^{-1}
[g]=\mathcal O(g):=\{g^x\;|\; x\in G\}\,\,,\,Stab(g)=G_g:=\{x\in G\;|\;g^x=g\}=Z(g)=C_G(g)
\left|\,[g]\,\right|=1\Longleftrightarrow [g]=\{g\}\Longleftrightarrow \,\forall \,x\in G\,\,,\,g^x=g\Longleftrightarrow\,\forall\,x\in G\,\,,\, xg=gx\Longleftrightarrow g\in Z(G)
|\mathcal O(x)|=[G:Stab(x)]=[G:G_x]\Longrightarrow\text{in our particular case}\,,\,|\mathcal O(x)|=\left[G:Z(g)\right]=\frac{|G|}{|Z(g)|}
|G|=\sum |\mathcal O(x)|=\sum_{x\in Z(G)}1+\sum_{x\notin Z(G)}|\mathcal O(x)|=|Z(G)|+\sum_{x\notin Z(G)}\frac{|G|}{|Z(x)|}
